The '''Instituto de Historia de Cuba''' in [[Havana]], [[Cuba]], is a [[research institute]], [[archive]], and library of late 19th and 20th century [[History of Cuba|Cuban history]]. It was established in 1987 under the [[Central Committee of the Communist Party of Cuba]]. It is located in the {{Interlanguage link multi|Palacio de Aldama|es}} near the {{Interlanguage link multi|Parque de la Fraternidad Americana|es}} in Havana.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ihc.cu/pages/quienes.php |accessdate=October 7, 2016 |title=Quiénes somos |publisher=Instituto de Historia de Cuba |location=Havana |language=es }}</ref> Among its collections are records related to [[Sergio Carbó y Morera]] and [[Ramón Grau]].{{sfn|Oliveira|2016}} Staff of the institute have included {{Interlanguage link multi|Oscar Zanetti|es}}, among others. According to its website, research focuses on topics such as Cuban economics, politics, society, regional history, and international relations.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ihc.cu/pages/lineas.php |accessdate=October 7, 2016 |title=Áreas y Líneas de Investigación del IHC |publisher=Instituto de Historia de Cuba |location=Havana |language=es }}</ref>

