The '''Clements Center for National Security''' is a nonpartisan policy and research center at the University of Texas at Austin.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.clementscenter.org/about|title=Who We Are – Clements Center for National Security|website=www.clementscenter.org|access-date=2016-05-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.statesman.com/news/news/ut-establishes-clements-center-for-study-of-diplom/nTqf3/|title=UT establishes Clements Center for study of diplomacy, security|website=www.statesman.com|access-date=2016-05-26}}</ref> The Center is named after former Texas Governor and Deputy Secretary of Defense [[Bill Clements]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.clementscenter.org/william-clements-jr|title=William P. Clements, Jr. – Clements Center for National Security|website=www.clementscenter.org|access-date=2016-05-24}}</ref>{{Infobox organization |image = | logo = | motto = Training the Next Generation of National Security Leaders |formation = 2013 |purpose= Nonpartisan Research and Policy Center |leader_title = Executive Director |leader_name = [[William Inboden]] | key_people = [[Paul D. Miller (academic)|Paul D. Miller]], [[Stephen Slick]], Mark Lawrence, and [[Robert M. Chesney]] |name = Clements Center for National Security |website = https://www.clementscenter.org/ | named_after = [[Bill Clements]] }}
